TY  - CONF
TI  - Deep Guard: A Multi-Modal Ensemble Deep Learning Framework for Real-Time Deepfake Detection and Proactive Content Authentication
AU  - Vardhini, Kondra Megha Nandi
AU  - Parthipan, V
AB  - The availability of high-tech deepfake tools creates new challenges to the integrity of digital content, and it is necessary to establish a detection and mitigation framework capable of handling more sophisticated technology. This research proposes a multi-level architecture of deepfake detection and mitigation that incorporates the most current Machine Learning (ML) models with the new forensic methods. The proposed approach plans a four-stage detection pipeline: preprocessing and feature extraction with MobileNetV3 and EfficientNet-B4 to analyze spatial information, a fusion-based classifier using ensemble classification combining XceptionNet, ResNet-50, and vision transformers, and mitigation by completing an adversarial training using GANs. The preprocessing step uses noise reduction and state-of-the-art algorithms of face alignment to normalize the input data. Feature extraction is a hybrid application that employs both computer vision methods and Deep Learning (DL) that extract low-level artifact features and high-level semantic features. The proposed DeepGuard employs the strategy of a weighted ensemble, which uses the results of several hyper-specific models to reach a higher precision level. Moreover, the mitigation phase uses preventative-like watermarking with strong steganographic practices and reactive-like filtering of content-based tracking. Experimental validations on Celeb-DF datasets have shown that it compares to the performance of other existing methods in that the proposed method achieves a detection accuracy of 98.8% with minimized false positives.
