TI  - A Robust Deepfake Detection Framework Using AV-CATNet for Audio-Visual Consistency and Temporal Attention in Secure Social Media Authentication
AU  - Anitha, G.
AU  - V, Aakash Saran
AU  - Loganathan, Nadish
AU  - R K, Arul Saravanan
AB  - The swift evolution of deepfakes with significant implications on the credibility of multimedia content in social media provides us with a stern challenge. Current detection strategies are typically inadequate in modeling cross-modal inconsistency and temporal information. To this end, we introduce AV-CATNet (Audio-Visual Cross-Attentional Transformer Network), which is an innovative deepfake detection system that utilizes cross-modal attention to synchronize lip movement with audio and temporal self-attention to detect sequence anomalies. AV-CATNet proposes the Fake Consistency Score (FCS), a transparent metric measuring the synchronization of audio and visual streams throughout history, making the model more transparent. In contrast to existing CNN, RNN, or late-fusion AV models, AV-CATNet reaches up to 97% accuracy on standard datasets such as DFDC, FakeAVCeleb, and FaceForensics++. It has an end-to-end attention-based fusion mechanism without the requirement for handcrafted features or post-processing. Designed to be optimized for real-time execution and edge deployment, AV-CATNet is a robust and scalable platform for content authentication, multimedia forensics, and deepfake defense in high-throughput social media scenarios.
