AU  - Vishnoi, Ankit
AB  - Deep learning caters to several sophisticated issues, which are analytics data and computer vision. It is also used for malware development that destroys security and confidentiality. Most of the surveys now in use are designed toward identifying deepfake content but the creation process is not well covered. Creating a DeepFake video is achieved using deep learning where a person in the actual video is replaced with another. DeepFakes can be identified through some of the deep learning-based techniques proposed in the literature. This paper expands on thorough explorations into DeepFake video detection and generation methods from 2023 - 2025 and explores their with a comparative analysis.
