AB  - The authenticity of deepfake content makes verification of authentic media extremely difficult because trust in information has completely vanished. A deepfake detection method combines style and content features through attention enhancement according to this study. Style features based on VGG-19 network and Gram matrices analyze face texture faults while FaceNet generates content features through optical flow and face embeddings. The MLP system uses attention modules to process tampered regions following a combination step of features. Research tests utilize FaceForensics++ DFS as well as DFDC and Celeb-DF benchmarks to establish high precision rates and generalization abilities. The real-time detection systems for deepfakes can use this method because it demonstrates both scalability for attack protection and automatic interpretation capabilities for detection purposes.
