AU  - Jadhav, Omkar Hindurao
AU  - Dalvi, Aaditya Sandeep
AU  - Sid, Shreekumar Santosh
AU  - Sarpate, Dikshendra Daulat
AB  - The proliferation of AI-driven voice synthesis technologies has introduced unprecedented risks to digital trust, particularly in cybersecurity, legal forensics, and authentication systems. This research proposes a dual-path binary classification model that combines deep learning (CNN-BiLSTM on melspectrograms) with traditional machine learning (wav2vec and MLP on LibROSA features) in an ensemble framework. Trained on 800 labeled samples (400 human, 400 cloned), also used various methods such as data augmentation, which was used to create around 7000 instances, the proposed system achieved 99.16 percent accuracy. A real-time Streamlit-based interface demonstrates its deployability. The results are statistically validated through five-fold cross-validation and confidence intervals. This work bridges spatial-temporal spectrogram learning with featurelevel interpretability to offer a scalable solution for AI-cloned voice detection.
