TI  - Towards Tamper-Resistant Digital Media: An AI and Blockchain Approach for Deepfake Detection
AU  - Sakthivel, K
AU  - N, Harine
AU  - G, Chandra Mohan
AB  - Deepfake technology poses severe risks to digital security and content authenticity due to advancements in generative models. Traditional detection methods rely on either visual or auditory cues, making them vulnerable to evolving forgery techniques and lacking secure validation. This study proposes a multimodal deepfake detection framework integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Blockchain for tamper-resistant verification. The system employs MTCNN and InceptionResNetV1 for visual forgery detection, and a CNN model on mel-spectrograms for audio deepfake identification. SHA-256 hashing and blockchain storage ensure the immutability and traceability of detection results. Experimental evaluation demonstrates that the proposed model achieves a detection accuracy of 93%, outperforming conventional CNN and hybrid CNN-LSTM systems in precision, recall, and F1-score. The framework provides a secure, scalable, and decentralized solution to detect synthetic media while preserving integrity and transparency, contributing to safer digital media ecosystems and reliable content authentication.
