TI  - DeepGuard: A Hybrid CNN-LSTM Framework for Robust Deepfake Video Detection with Spatiotemporal Analysis
AU  - Cyril, Madda Anthony
AU  - Prakash Sunkavalli, Jaya
AU  - Prasanth, Dodla
AB  - Deepfake technology has developed very quickly, allowing highly realistic artificial media to be created that causes serious risks to privacy, security, and disinformation. This paper introduces a deep learning method for identifying deepfake videos by applying a hybrid Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) model. The proposed model takes advantage of spatial information learned by a CNN (Xception backbone) and temporal relationships learned by an LSTM in order to label videos as real or fake. The model was trained on the FaceForensics++ dataset and evaluated on the Celeb-DF dataset with an accuracy of 82%. A web application was also implemented for real-time deepfake detection. The outcome proves the efficacy of the suggested architecture in detecting manipulated videos with challenges and future enhancements
