TY  - CONF
TI  - DeepFake Detection Using EfficientNetB3 and RestNet18
AU  - More, Prajwal
AU  - D, Evangeline
AU  - M, Sinthuja
AB  - DeepFake videos-AI-generated content that convincingly simulates human faces and speech-pose serious threats to digital media integrity and public trust. To address the growing need for reliable DeepFake detection, this paper proposes a spatio-temporal framework that integrates both visual appearance and motion dynamics. Our method employs adaptive keyframe selection, face alignment, dense optical flow via RAFT, and supervised contrastive learning to capture temporal inconsistencies between real and manipulated content. We evaluate two deep convolutional neural networks: EfficientNet-B3 and ResNet18. While EfficientNet-B3 demonstrates strong classification accuracy and generalization across video manipulations, ResNet18 underperforms, particularly under motion distortions. Comparative results highlight the value of using richer architectures with motion-aware representations for robust forgery detection. Our study presents an effective, interpretable, and computationally feasible framework for DeepFake detection, suitable for both forensic analysis and future real-time deployment.
