TI  - TemporalFormer: Enhanced EfficientFormer for Real-Time Deepfake Detection on Edge Devices
AU  - Zafar, Aarif
AU  - Singh, Kartik
AU  - Manav, Udit
AU  - Panda, Rajesh Kumar
AU  - Sahni, Nikhil
AU  - Nair, Renju Chirakarotu
AB  - The rapid proliferation of deepfake videos, forged multimedia, tampered contents across social media and other communication platforms poses significant challenges to digital security and information authenticity, necessitating effective detection mechanisms, particularly on mobile platforms. Deepfake videos increasingly undermine digital trust, but most detection methods depend on resource-heavy cloud systems, unsuitable for real-time use on edge devices. We present TemporalFormer, an enhanced EfficientFormerV2 model, optimized for fast and accurate deepfake detection directly on mobile and edge platforms. TemporalFormer analyzes video streams by extracting 30 equidistant frames from a 6 -second window by capturing a frame from live screen at 200 ms intervals and processing a batch of 30 frames in single prediction. This enables real-time processing of dynamic content like video calls, social media feeds, and video conferences. This lightweight framework integrates EfficientFormerV2’s feature extraction with positional encoding and a 1D CNN layer to model temporal dependencies, achieving an inference time of 20 ms per batch. Trained and tested on Celeb-df(v2), TemporalFormer attains an accuracy of 93.2 % and an AUC of 0.90, while demonstrating robust generalization with an AUC of 0.87 on the FaceForensics++ dataset during crosscorpora analysis, surpassing baselines such as Xception and EfficientNet-B0 in both performance and efficiency. By offering a scalable, offline solution, TemporalFormer enables robust, ondevice video forensics for resource-constrained environments.
