TI  - A Frequency Aware Attention Driven Deepfake Detection Framework Using YOLOv8
AU  - Sunil, Reshma
AU  - Mer, Parita
AU  - Parmar, Parth
AB  - The rapid advancement of generative adversarial networks (GANs) has resulted in an increase in the development of extremely realistic deepfake content., posing serious threats to digital media integrity and public trust. In response to the limitations of spatial domain only analysis in existing detection methods, this paper introduces a novel framework that integrates a Frequency Aware Attention mechanism into the YOLOv8 architecture for robust and efficient deepfake image detection. The proposed model jointly leverages spatial and frequency domain cues to enhance feature discrimination, enabling it to capture subtle inconsistencies introduced during image synthesis. By incorporating frequency aware attention modules, the framework directs the model's focus toward high frequency artifacts and manipulation traces often overlooked by traditional detectors. YOLOv8 ensures real time detection capabilities with high precision, making the system suitable for deployment in practical surveillance and content moderation scenarios. Experimental evaluations conducted on OpenForensics dataset demonstratethat our approach outperforms previous baseline models with a state-of-the-art accuracy of 98.74 % while keeping inference time low. This research underscores the value of combining frequency insights with attention driven architectures for effective deepfake detection.
