AB  - Deepfakes are the manipulated media which includes images, videos and audio, created using advanced Deep Learning (DL) techniques such as face-swapping algorithms, Generative Adversarial Network (GANs) and diffusion models. Advanced deep learning methods allow creation of the content that looks highly realistic and enables a way to misuse for political agendas, defaming people and also for the entertainment. The created fakes easily blend facial expressions and movements which creates a confusion among the people when they see themselves in the places they never been or the things that they haven't done. Generating fake content is convincingly easy now with usage of the advanced AI techniques, therefore this results in the spread of misinformation and breaks the societal trust. To overcome this situation the researchers have implemented many deepfake detection models using DL techniques. Also, techniques like multimodal analysis, attention mechanisms and fusion strategies are faster compared to the traditional detection methods. The outcomes demonstrate that DL models are wellsuited for detection and classification of deepfake content across various media formats.
