TI  - EfficientNet and Vision Transformer Fusion for High-Precision Deepfake Image Identification
AU  - Talasila, Srinivas
AU  - Gurrala, Vijaya Kumar
AU  - Matta, Varshini
AU  - Musthyala, Madhuri
AU  - Balla, Siva Sai
AB  - The increasing menace of deepfake image content requires strong real-time detection mechanisms to ensure digital trust and avoid misinformation. This paper introduces a hybrid deep learning architecture that combines EfficientNet-B0 and Vision Transformer (ViT) to detect deepfakes with improved spatial and semantic feature extraction. The CNN part extracts fine-grained local textures, while the Transformer captures global relationships, allowing the model to detect subtle manipulations effectively. The outputs of both branches are fused and used as input to a fully connected classifier for binary classification. Experimental results indicate that the model has a high accuracy of 99.9% during training, with validation accuracy plateauing at 98.52% and test accuracy at 92.20%, showing excellent generalization capability of the model. The system is further validated using real-time deployment in the form of a Flask-based web application for live webcam detection. This accurate hybrid model balances performance and precision, bringing a scalable and interpretable approach to the world of deepfake detection.
