TI  - FaceTrace: Leveraging Motion Patterns for Deepfake Video Authentication
AU  - RS, Ramya
AU  - Narayankar, Karuna
AB  - This paper presents a deep learning system for deepfake video detection based on a hybrid spatio-temporal model that integrates ResNeXt-50 and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks. Spatial features are extracted from face regions by a pretrained ResNeXt-50 CNN, while temporal evolution between video frames is modelled by LSTM layers. The system features a web-based interface built with Flask to enable the user to upload videos and dynamically manage the frame sampling rate. The system analyses input videos by cropping and detecting faces, extracting frames, and classifying content as Real or Fake based on temporal face inconsistencies. Prediction confidence scores are produced, and outputs are visualized in frame-wise bounding boxes and heatmaps. Experimental results demonstrate the model's high accuracy of 98.5% and confidence for real-time deepfake detection. This approach demonstrates the effectiveness of combining convolutional and recurrent neural networks for tackling video-based forgery detection tasks.
