AU  - Baviskar, Om
AU  - Patil, Rachana Yogesh
AB  - The multifaceted challenges in the advancement of deepfake detection and generation technologies include legal, ethical, and technical issues, as well as insufficient infrastructure and inadequate regulatory policies worldwide. To provide an unbiased perspective on the research scenario of deepfake detection and generation, a quantitative evaluation of the research papers in this field published between 2010 and 2024 has been performed. The top five countries of research contribution include USA, China, UK, India, and Germany with remarkable progresses in CNN, GANs and transfer learning methods. Unluckily, a number of these countries have been observed to have a high research output but little interconnectivity between them. The future work in this paper discusses the research directions in deepfake detection which include the combination of the AI-based models, ethical approach to AI governance, and enhancing the real-time deepfake detection in multimedia.
