AU  - Thalor, Meenakshi
AU  - Rangila, Mohammed Munawwar
AU  - Pawar, Mehul
AU  - Parihar, Priyamvada
AU  - Kharat, Yash
AB  - The rapid development of deep learning techniques has facilitated the creation of hyper realistic videos, but has also created significant challenges in their discovery. These videos generated by AI often lack visual clues that they have been manipulated, making them difficult to detect by traditional methods. This study introduces deep learning techniques that use convolutional neural network (CNN) to capture features from a frame and recurrent neural network (RNN) to identify consistent nonlinearities from body to body across frames. Our method can extract subtle differences by working on consecutive lines by combining spatial and temporal features, thereby enhancing the detection ability. This method improves the accuracy and robustness of identifying fake video content, leading to ongoing discussions about real content in the age of artificial intelligence technology.
