TI  - Lightweight and Efficient Deepfake Detection Using Transfer-Learned MobileNetV2
AU  - Nayak, Debasish
AU  - Prasad Mishra, Bhabani Shankar
AU  - Champati Rai, Satyananda
AB  - Deepfakes, produced through advanced generative models, threaten the authenticity of digital media. This study presents a lightweight deepfake detection framework utilising transfer-learned MobileNetV2, designed for efficient deployment on resource-constrained platforms. The model is trained on a Kaggle-sourced dataset of pre-cropped facial frames, incorporating extensive data augmentation and fine-tuning to enhance generalisation. Compared with other compact networks, including ResNet18 and MesoNet, MobileNetV2 achieves superior performance with a test accuracy of 98.23%, while maintaining a compact architecture ( 3.4M parameters) suitable for real-time inference. These results underline MobileNetV2’s effectiveness for scalable and edge-based deepfake detection, with future improvements aimed at temporal consistency and adversarial robustness.
