TY  - CONF
TI  - DeepFakeShield: AI-Based Detection of Deepfake Videos and Synthetic Media
AU  - P, Kumar
AU  - Ramya, S. Thanga
AU  - Paul, T Sam
AU  - S, Senthil Pandi
AB  - The advancement of deep generative models has enabled the creation of highly realistic manipulated videos, commonly referred to as deepfakes, which pose unprecedented threats to digital security, media credibility, and public trust. As these synthetic media artifacts become more convincing, traditional detection methods are proving inadequate, creating an urgent need for advanced and explainable AI-driven approaches. With generative models producing increasingly realistic manipulations, conventional detection methods are no longer sufficient. To address this challenge, we introduce DeepFakeShield, an AI-based detection framework that integrates deep learning architectures with explainability mechanisms for reliable and transparent identification of manipulated videos. Unlike conventional binary classifiers, DeepFakeShield places strong emphasis on interpretability, ensuring that outputs can be justified and trusted in legal, investigative, and journalistic contexts. By focusing on the temporal coherence of lip movements, spatial consistency of facial features, and detection of low-level artifacts, the framework provides a multi-layered defense against both lowquality and highly sophisticated deepfake attacks. Furthermore, its modular design supports adaptability across various media formats and deployment environments, ranging from digital forensic laboratories to real-time social media monitoring pipelines. The inclusion of explainability mechanisms not only improves accountability but also empowers human analysts to verify AI decisions, thereby bridging the gap between automation and expert validation. Extensive evaluations demonstrate that the system achieves high accuracy in distinguishing authentic videos from manipulated ones while maintaining computational efficiency suitable for large-scale deployment. With its modular architecture and explainabilitydriven design, DeepFakeShield provides not only automated detection but also transparent reasoning, enabling effective defense against synthetic media and contributing to the preservation of content authenticity in an era of AI-driven misinformation.
