TI  - Deepfake Hunter: A Multimodal Detection Framework
AU  - Thatipamula, Ajay
AU  - Patidar, Mukesh
AU  - Gandi, Mukesh
AU  - Nandayala, Lila Shankar Naidu
AU  - Kommula, Datta Sai Krishna
AU  - Dontha, Vishnu Vardhan
AB  - Deepfakes represent a growing challenge in digital forensics, as they generate highly convincing synthetic audiovisual content using deep learning models. While these technologies have legitimate applications in media production and accessibility, their misuse for misinformation, identity manipulation, and privacy breaches raises serious concerns. This work introduces Deepfake Hunter, a systems-engineered multimodal detection framework designed to ensure reliability, interpretability, and scalable deployment. The proposed architecture integrates three complementary modules: (1) a visual encoder based on XceptionNet to extract spatial inconsistencies, (2) an audio encoder utilizing InceptionResNetV2 on Constant-Q Transform (CQT) spectrograms for spectral analysis, and (3) an attention- driven recurrent unit to capture temporal coherence. The system emphasizes modular interfaces between preprocessing, feature extraction, fusion, and classification layers, supporting deployment across both cloud and edge environments. Experiments on benchmark datasets Face Forensics++, CelebDF, DFDC, and Fake AV Cele demonstrate that Deepfake Hunter achieves superior accuracy and robustness compared with unimodal detectors, highlighting its potential as a dependable framework for real- world multimedia authenticity verification.
