TI  - A Hybrid EfficientNet-TSM Framework for Deepfake Detection in Digital Media Content
AU  - V, Pooja S
AU  - D, Keerthika
AU  - Subbalakshmi, S.
AU  - Sangeetha, V.
AB  - Deepfakes are an increasing concern for privacy, trust and security of digital media since they make it possible to create high-fidelity but fake content. We propose a Hybrid EfficientNet-Temporal Shift Module TSM framework which can learn spatial and temporal features to improve the detection of deepfakes in images and videos. EfficientNet is able to capture subtle visual artifacts in manipulated images, while TSM captures motion inconsistencies across video frames in a lightweight and efficient way. We also use Grad-CAM to enhance interpretability by visualizing regions of an image or video that contributed to a classification decision and shows how the model is processing manipulated content. Our experiments demonstrate that our framework achieves higher accuracy, scalability, and robustness than traditional CNN–RNN methods, while supporting forensic use through its efficiency, interpretability, and ability to strengthen trust in digital media to promote user trust.
