TI  - Towards Robust Deepfake Audio Detection: A Hybrid CNN-Transformer Approach with XAI
AU  - Mundik, Mayuresh
AU  - Jadhav, Archana
AU  - Yerkal, Aditya
AU  - Tambe, Kunal
AU  - Kamthe, Siddhesh
AB  - Deepfakes, realistic media generated by AI, have often been linked to the spread of misinformation and even digital crimes. These synthetic creations can take the form of audio, video, or images. While a lot of research has gone into spotting fake videos and images, audio deepfakes haven't received nearly as much attention. This is especially concerning as voice-generation technology continues to advance rapidly with the growth of AI. In this survey, we explore the latest methods for both creating and detecting deepfakes, with a particular focus on audio. We look at a range of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques that are currently being used in this space. We also propose a hybrid model that combines Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Transformers, supported by Explainable AI (XAI) tools to make the system more transparent and trustworthy. To make the model even more resilient against sophisticated attacks, we suggest incorporating adversarial training methods like FGSM and PGD.
