TI  - A Novel Multi-Layer Framework for Human and AI-Voice Detection Using Machine Learning and Network Architecture
AU  - Rayat, Simar Singh
AU  - Thapa, Sujal
AU  - Basnet, Raj
AU  - Sharma, Vikrant
AU  - Dahiya, Susheela
AU  - Rathod, Arun Pratap Singh
AB  - The rapid advancement in the field of Artificial Intelligence has led to the development of AI-voice systems capable of delivering informative conversations, including factual, general, and even emotionally adaptive responses. However, some individuals have exploited these systems for self-serving purposes. Traditional methods lack the capability to distinguish between human and AI voices, causing a potential leading to an increase in fraudulent and unethical activities, thereby creating an urgent need for a more advanced solution. To address this limitation, we propose our framework that integrates Machine Learning techniques with an adversarial reverse engineering framework equipped with a multi-layered decision architecture incorporating feature extraction and source utility handling. The proposed framework aims to provide real-time edge processing, equipped with adversarial robustness and supporting multilingual capabilities. It handles multiple edge cases such as data cleansing and content moderation by leveraging architectures including convolutional neural networks (abbreviated as CNN), recurrent neural networks (abbreviated as RNN), Transformers, and other specific techniques. The model was evaluated under multiple edge cases, such as content and linguistic variations, adversarial and deceptive inputs, synthetic and contextual channel effects, using publicly accessible datasets such as Standard Speech & TTS, Fake-or-Real, ASVspoof 2019, and MLAAD. The proposed framework achieved an accuracy of 92.18% for classifying human and AI voices and report generation and distinctly classified other factors such as an equal error rate (abbreviated as EER) of about 6.8%, recall of around 93.16%, and F1-score around 92.84%, confirming the effectiveness of the proposed innovative solution in both detection accuracy and robustness.
