TI  - Wavelet Scattering and Spectral Feature Fusion for Robust Voice Liveness Detection
AU  - Liu, Yanchang
AU  - Zhao, Zehao
AU  - Lu, Hao
AU  - Zhang, Kun
AU  - Dong, Jiaqi
AU  - Tong, Jinlong
AB  - The growing threat of audio-based spoofing, such as replay, speech synthesis, and voice conversion, has created an urgent demand for reliable voice liveness detection (VLD) in speaker verification and voice assistant systems. We propose a novel VLD method that integrates wavelet scattering transform (WST) with complementary spectral representations, including MEL spectrogram, constant-Q transform (CQT), spectral flatness, and speech energy entropy rate (SEER). These features are fused and evaluated using both lightweight and deep convolutional neural networks: a custom residual CNN, MobileNetV2, ResNet18, and ResNet34. Comprehensive experiments on the ASVspoof 2021 benchmark, covering logical access (LA), physical access (PA), and deepfake (DF) subsets, demonstrate that WST-based fusion consistently outperforms existing approaches. Our ResNet34+WSTCQT model achieves state-of-the-art results, including a perfect 0.000 EER on PA and competitive performance on DF (0.020 EER) and LA (0.041 EER). MobileNetV2 configurations also outperform strong baselines like ECAPA-TDNN and W2V2+LCNN+BLSTM. The results confirm the effectiveness and generalizability of our approach across spoofing types and model sizes. This work provides a scalable, low-latency, and accurate front-end for future real-time audio authentication systems.
