TI  - CapsNet–CNN: AI-Powered Voice Authentication System for Secure Online Banking Transactions
AU  - Arumugam, Vinoth Kumar
AU  - Gowri, A
AU  - Ravichandran, Susmethaa Siri
AU  - Kushwah, Dileep Singh
AU  - Vengaimarbhan, D.
AU  - Chandrasekar, T.
AB  - There is a need to apply spoofing and malicious attack-resistant biometric authentication solutions to protect financial information retained in online banking systems. This paper presents a scheme for efficient voice authentication that utilizes a blend of CapsNets and CNNs. The scheme efficiently extracts speaker-specific audio patterns and spatial hierarchies using Mel-spectrogram representations, as opposed to sequential models. A proprietary dataset of over 15,000 utterances collected in a multitude of contexts is used for training and validation. An adversarial voiceprint perturbation module and an anti-spoofing branch are incorporated within the model in order to recognize manipulated or forged voice inputs. Experimental results outperform the LSTM and x-vector baselines in terms of improved spoof resistance, with an accuracy of 97.83%, an equal error rate of 1.78%, and a detection accuracy of 96.91%. The method is apt for use in mobile banking applications due to its real-time voice authentication speed and security.
