TY  - CONF
TI  - Computational Social Engineering Attacks Mitigation in Social Media Platforms
AU  - Lungu, Nelson
AU  - Barik, Lalbihari
AU  - AlRababah, Ahmad AbdulQuadir
AU  - Rout, Suchismita
AU  - Saini, Jatinderkumar R.
AU  - Patra, Sudhansu Shekhar
AB  - Considerable attacks on the security and privacy of users have been achieved using advanced computational social engineering methods to manipulate the psychological factors in using automated systems by using social media platforms as a primary vehicle to gather intelligence on victims. The measures that are currently being implemented to mitigate cyber-attacks are mainly based on conventional cybersecurity protection and pay little attention to their psychological and behavioral aspects. The study demonstrates an original hybrid design to include deep learning-based behavioral modeling and real-time psychological profiling to identify and reduce the threat of computational social engineering across social media. We use convolutional neural networks to analyse material, recurrent neural networks to simulate time-related behaviour, and attention techniques to grasp context. Experimental validation shows a 94.7% increase in detection accuracy and \mathbf9 2. 3 % increase in precision and recall over existing approaches. The system detects manipulation patterns using multidimensional multi-linguistic characteristics, social network analysis, and temporal interaction patterns, providing substantial defence against increasingly diversified attack vectors.
